==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: cromorna
<hw>cro*mor"na</hw> <pr>(kr⟦osl⟧*m⟦ocir⟧r"n⟦adot⟧)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[F. <ets>cromorne</ets> (cf. It. <ets>cromorno</ets>), fr. G.
<ets>krummhorn</ets> crooked horn, cornet, an organ pipe turned like a
trumpet; <ets>krumm</ets> crooked + <ets>horn</ets> horn.]</ety>
<fld>(Mus.)</fld> <def>A certain reed stop in the organ, of a quality of
tone resembling that of the oboe.</def> <altsp>[Corruptly written
<asp>cromona</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cromwell</ent>⟦br⟧
